{
  "texts": [
    "Initially, 305 students were asked to participate in performing a graphomotor test, where each student has to write or draw specific predefined shapes or figures called stimuli on the paper attached to the screen of the tablet.",
    "Numerous features including time duration of the stimulus, duration of a stroke, duration of lift, velocity, jerk, Renyi Entropy of order 2, signal to noise ratio, etc.",
    "were extracted from the raw data for further anal-ysis.",
    "Various machine learning algorithms including SVM [61], random forest, MLP [63], Extra Trees, Gaussian Naïve Bayes [64], Ada Boost, etc.",
    "are utilized in the proposed work for analyzing the features."
  ]
}